summary: SWR Episode 10 Review
body:
SWR Episode 10 Review

We got a Torra episode with this one! Honestly, I was excited, because she’s one of my favorite characters so far. It was also nice to see how it turned out with Kaz’s mission. I wonder what Doza’s connection with the First Order is, especially now we know he was a part of the Empire.

Also, I was NOT expecting Rucklin to appear (it’s probably gonna be that way for the next few episodes he’s set to appear in. 😜), but he had an interesting role in this episode. I kinda feel bad for all the chores he has to do, especially serving Hype, who is kind of annoying to be honest. I’m not sure how long Rucklin will be salty towards Kaz, but that still doesn’t make me suspect that he’s the First Order spy as mentioned in the first episode. Honestly, it could be ANYONE at this point in the series (Doza, Torra, Rucklin, Hype, etc.). But if the spy’s identity is revealed later in the series, don’t tell me please!
